{
  "texts": [
    "Based on the numbers in the confusion matrix, which shows how well the classifier performed on the test data, these parameters are determined.",
    "These evaluation parameters are computed using the values of TP (true positive), TN (true negative), FP (false positive), and FN (false negative), whose values range from 0 (minimum) to 1 (maximum).",
    "The accuracy of a classifier's predictions of both positive and negative classes is measured.",
    "Mathematically,",
    "Precision and recall are two regularly used assessment criteria for classifier performance."
  ]
}